The paper deals with the task of identifying relationships between items in the domain of clothing recommendation, which involves handling high-dimensional and semantically complicated features. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of embeddings to learn richer notions of compatibility, which suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with large-scale compatibility prediction tasks, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
